\/p95VHY-8Aj","jetpack_sharing_enabled":true,"jetpack-related-posts":[{"id":32976,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/07\/30\/forgives-between-salat\/","url_meta":{"origin":33003,"position":0},"title":"Hadith on Wudu: Allah forgives what one did between prayers","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 30, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Uthman ibn Affan reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cA Muslim man does not perform ablution in an excellent manner and then performs prayer, but that Allah will forgive him for what occurred between his prayer and the next.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 158, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":14001,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/05\/06\/wudu-sins-erased\/","url_meta":{"origin":33003,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Wudu: Excellent ablution erases minor sins","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 6, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Uthman ibn Affan reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cWhoever performs ablution in an excellent manner, his sins will depart from his body even from under his fingernails.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 245 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Muslim \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0639\u064f\u062b\u0652\u0645\u064e\u0627\u0646\u064e \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0639\u064e\u0641\u064e\u0651\u0627\u0646\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":14284,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/05\/19\/wudu-salat-expiate-sins\/","url_meta":{"origin":33003,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Salah: Excellent ablution, prayer erases minor sins","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 19, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Uthman ibn Affan reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \"No Muslim attends a prescribed prayer and performs its ablution, reverence, and bowing in the best manner, but that it will be an expiation for his previous sins as long as he did not commit\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":14009,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/05\/06\/waiting-prayer-fortress\/","url_meta":{"origin":33003,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Masjid: Waiting for consecutive prayers","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 6, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cShall I not tell you of a deed by which Allah expiates your sins and raises your status?\u201d They said, \u201cOf course, O Messenger of Allah.\u201d The Prophet said, \u201cThorough ablution despite difficulty, taking many steps\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":32995,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/07\/30\/waiting-salat-in-jamaah\/","url_meta":{"origin":33003,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Masajid: Waiting in between congregational prayers expiates sins","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 30, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Ali reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cShall I not tell you of that by which Allah expiates sins? Thorough ablution despite hardship, working your feet in walking to the mosque, and waiting in between prayers will fully cleanse one of sins.\u201d Source: Musnad al-Bazza\u0304r 505\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":15799,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/08\/23\/attend-sermon-quietly\/","url_meta":{"origin":33003,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Jumuah: Minor sins forgiven until next Friday","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 23, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cWhoever performs ablution in the best manner, comes to Friday prayer, and listens while remaining quiet, his\u00a0sins will be forgiven until the next Friday and an additional three days, but whoever plays with pebbles has behaved\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]}],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/33003","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/w